<activity xml:id="absolute_extrema-fluency-checkit">
    <statement>
        <p> 
Explain how to find the absolute minimum and absolute maximum values of the
function <m>f(x)=-2 \, x^{3} + 18 \, x^{2} + 42 \, x + 33</m> on the interval <m>[-2,2]</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
The absolute extrema may occur at these <m>x</m>-values:
<m>-2, -1, 2</m>.
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><p><m>f(-2)=37</m></p></li>
            <li><p><m>f(-1)=11</m></p></li>
            <li><p><m>f(2)=173</m></p></li>
        </ul>
        <p>
Thus the absolute minimum is <m>11</m> and the absolute
maximum is <m>173</m>.
        </p>
        <p>
(The value <m>f(7)=523</m>
is ignored as <m>7</m> isn't in the given interval.)
        </p>
    </answer>
    </activity>
    
    
